sysResourceCpuTable.name: sysResourceCpuTable
sysResourceCpuTable.description: This table defines the CPus present within the system.

sysResSlotID.name: sysResSlotID
sysResSlotID.description: The slot for which this CPU information pertains.

sysResCpuIndex.name: sysResCpuIndex
sysResCpuIndex.description: An identifier for the CPU on a per slot basis.

sysResCpuSpeed.name: sysResCpuSpeed
sysResCpuSpeed.description: The speed of the processor in mega-hertz.

sysResCpuID.name: sysResCpuID
sysResCpuID.description: A system wide unique identifier for each CPU.

sysResInstalledLocalMemory.name: sysResInstalledLocalMemory
sysResInstalledLocalMemory.description: Total installed local memory 'DRAM' used for code and data. This is reported in mega-bytes.

sysResUsedLocalMemory.name: sysResUsedLocalMemory
sysResUsedLocalMemory.description: The current amount of local memory 'DRAM' that is currently being used for code and data. This is reported in bytes.

sysResourceTable.name: sysResourceTable
sysResourceTable.description: This table describes total installed system resources.

sysResourceEntry.name: sysResourceEntry
sysResourceEntry.description: Describes a particular installed set of system resources.

sysResInstalledNvram.name: sysResInstalledNvram
sysResInstalledNvram.description: The total installed non-volatile memory 'NVRAM'. This is reported in K-bytes.

sysResInstalledFlash.name: sysResInstalledFlash
sysResInstalledFlash.description: The total installed flash memory. This is reported in K-bytes.

sysResInstalledSharedMemory.name: sysResInstalledSharedMemory
sysResInstalledSharedMemory.description: The total amount of shared memory that is installed. This is reported in K-bytes.

sysResUsedNvram.name: sysResUsedNvram
sysResUsedNvram.description: The current amount of non-volatile memory 'NVRAM' that is currently being used for data. This is reported in bytes.

sysResUsedFlash.name: sysResUsedFlash
sysResUsedFlash.description: The current amount of flash memory that is currently being used for code and data. This is reported in bytes.

sysResUsedSharedMemory.name: sysResUsedSharedMemory
sysResUsedSharedMemory.description: The current amount of shared memory that is currently being used for data. This is reported in bytes.

sysResManagementCpuResource.name: sysResManagementCpuResource
sysResManagementCpuResource.description: The desired amount of CPU bandwith reserved for management purposes. For example, in the default state (1), the device will devote all CPU bandwith to switching if necessary therefore possibly dropping management frames. If limited (2) is selected, management of the device may appear slow while under maximum switching capabilities although management will still be possible which may result in dropped frames. If full (3) is selected, management of the device is always possible and acts as if there is no switching load on the device, which may result in dropped frames.

switchLoad.name: switchLoad
switchLoad.description: The returned value represents the current switch load based upon a percentage of maximum switching capacity where maximum switching capacity is 100%.

peakSwitchload.name: peakSwitchload
peakSwitchload.description: The peak load which has occured on this switch. The value returned represents The peak percentage of switch load based upon a percentage of maximum switch load which is 100%.

peakSwitchLoadTime.name: peakSwitchLoadTime
peakSwitchLoadTime.description: The time at which the peak switch load occured. The value returned will represent system up time at which the peak occured.

peakSwitchClear.name: peakSwitchClear
peakSwitchClear.description: This object is used to clear the values found in peakSwitchload and peakSwitchLoadTime. When set with a value of clear(1) the values will be cleared. When read, a value of noClear(2) will be returned. A set of noClear(2) will have no effect.
